{{pagebanner|European quarter WV banner.jpg|pgname=Business District}} The '''Business District''' is a district in [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]].
==Get in== {{Mapframe|50.8621|4.3562|zoom=14}} {{mapshapes|Q506298}}<!--metro--> {{Mapshapes|Q117965|stroke-width=2}} <!-- Brussels S-train --> This area is on the northern side of the city, not far from the central district.
==See== [[File:Endives au marché.jpg|thumb|right|''Witloof'', a popular vegetable accidentally "invented" in the botanical garden of Brussels]] * {{see | name=Botanical Garden | alt=Kruidtuin | url=http://botanique.be/en | email=info@botanique.be | address=Koningsstraat 236 | lat=50.85437 | long=4.36497 | directions={{rint|brussels|metro}} {{rint|brussels|2}}{{rint|brussels|6}} {{station| Kruidtuin|61|92|93}} | phone=+32 2 218 37 32 | tollfree= | hours= | price=Free | wikipedia=Botanical Garden of Brussels | wikidata=Q739334 |image=Botanique 01.JPG | lastedit=2018-05-18 | content=The original botanical garden is used as a park and its greenhouse as a concert venue. It started in the 18th century as a small plot in the garden of the former palace of Prince Charles Alexander of Lorraine, but it became under threat in 1826 when the Royal Library and several other projects sought to reclaim the area. To preserve the collection, a collective of herbalists and botanists acquired a new plot of land just outside the city walls, which by then consisted of a collection of ponds, woods and allotments. The area was reorganized by architect Charles-Henri Petersen, and opened as the botanical garden of the city in 1829, just before Belgium gained its independence. The garden saw expansions in 1842 and 1854 and became popular among locals who, in those days, did not have the opportunity to travel, and saw many exotic plants in the garden for the first time. Although the garden was sponsored by the government from 1837 onwards, mismanagement caused the garden to slip into debt, and the owners were forced to sell land to allow construction of the North Station, and also started to sell off the botanical collection itself, which endangered the original didactic and scientific purposes of the garden. The government intervened and purchased the garden in 1870, thereby preserving its panorama and function as a park and for scientific purporses. Many areas saw reconstruction, and many decorations, rock arrangements, greenhouses etc. date from this period. The garden flourished and remained popular, but became under increased pressure by civil construction projects, most notably the expansion of the North-South railway link, the expansing of the inner ring causeway after the city walls were demolished, and the St. Lazare street which slices the park. It became impossible to maintain the botanical collection, and it was decided to move it to Meise, a town to the North of Brussels near [[Grimbergen]]. The park underwent its last restauration in 1958 for the World Fair, when architect René Pechère harmonized it after the relocation of much of the collection to Meise. It became a protected monument in 1964. Curiously, the botanical garden is credited with the invention of ''witloof'', a local specialty, and the dark outgrowns of chicory. According to an urban legend, ''witloof'' was first created in the mushroom cellar of the botanical garden when Frans Breziers forced chicory to grow in the dark in 1850. ''Witloof'' is nowadays a popular vegetable in Brussels and Flanders, and can be purchased in most grocery stores in season. Its white leaves are refreshing and crunchy, although they have a rather bitter taste. It can be eaten fresh, or takes on a sweeter taste after cooking. }} * {{see | name=North Station building | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=50.860278 | long=4.360833 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q660792 | content=Erected in an Art Déco style. }} * {{see | name=Museum Kanal (Centre Pompidou) | alt= | url=http://kanal.brussels/en | email=info@kanal.brussels | address=Akenkaai | lat=50.85952 | long=4.34861 | directions= | phone=+32 2 435 13 60 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=12:00-22:00, closed on Tuesdays | price=€14 | content=Museum for modern art in a former Citroën showroom. }} * {{see | name=Tour & Taxis | alt=Thurn en taxi | url=https://tour-taxis.com/ | email= | address= | lat=50.864444 | long=4.348056 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q2320851 | lastedit=2022-11-29 | content=Old industrial site, converted to multi use. Including a food market, business center, shops. }}
==Do== On the east side of the North Station, the Brussels '''Red Light District''' occupies Aarschot St. and surrounding streets. * {{do | name=Brasserie de la Senne | alt= | url=http://www.brasseriedelasenne.be/ | email= | address= | lat=50.868 | long=4.34905 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q2196984 | lastedit=2022-11-29 | content=Brewery, beer tasting and shop. }} * {{do | name=Ferme du parc maximilien | alt=Boerderij van het Maximiliaanpark | url=http://www.lafermeduparcmaximilien.be/ | email= | address= | lat=50.85856 | long=4.35007 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q110041201 | lastedit=2022-11-29 | content= }}
==Buy==
==Eat== Plenty of overpriced veggie bars around the district, and a number shops in the station building as well.
==Drink== When you're waiting for a connecting coach, the {{marker|type=drink|name=Starbucks|lat=50.85998|long=4.35963}} inside the North Station can offer warmth and power sockets; you are not obliged to buy their overpriced drinks.
* {{drink | name=Botanique | url=http://botanique.be/ | email= | address=Koningsstraat 236 | lat=50.85464 | long=4.36620 | directions={{station|Kruidtuin|2|6|92|93}} | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=The place for rock and pop. They do, on occasion, bring more experimental acts. }}
==Sleep== ===Mid-range=== * {{sleep | name=Thon Hotel Brussels City Centre | url=http://www.thonhotels.com/brusselscitycentre | email= | address=Avenue du Boulevard-Boulevardlaan 17 | lat=50.856005 | long=4.357399 | directions= | phone=+32 2 205-15-11 | tollfree= | fax=+32 2 201-15-15 | checkin= | checkout= | price=€69+ | content=Major 4-star hotel in the centre of Brussels with 454 rooms. }}
== Stay safe == Do not venture too far away from the Nord-Noord station and the surrounding business district because several rough areas are nearby, including the red light district.
==Go next== * Directly south of the business district is the Brussels '''[[Brussels/Pentagon|Pentagon]]''' district.
{{outlinedistrict}} {{Mapmask | 50.858701239679924,4.34624065819702 | 50.85949034566167,4.345720404982567 | 50.86021836248773,4.343960875868797 | 50.860733046594724,4.344540233016015 | 50.86167097604826,4.346331948637962 | 50.862986955464606,4.347508979518906 | 50.8649355,4.3417045 | 50.865756,4.3423545 | 50.8672106,4.3435069 | 50.8676007,4.3435928 | 50.8680232,4.343464 | 50.8683542,4.343254 | 50.86931253903038,4.342303265333176 | 50.86968836184934,4.342743943891484 | 50.8700286,4.3431429 | 50.8699749,4.3443768 | 50.8712638,4.3480571 | 50.8701897,4.3514184 | 50.8726063,4.3573537 | 50.8723243,4.3593322 | 50.87182446626648,4.360574473142624 | 50.86503314910866,4.355285156965256 | 50.86589989271584,4.3569266688823705 | 50.865547780068866,4.358160485029221 | 50.865574862365804,4.359523052573205 | 50.86548683383966,4.36136304795742 | 50.86320480896718,4.360284794569016 | 50.862920394056594,4.3618190181255345 | 50.86258857446809,4.363546360731125 | 50.85851174108087,4.361658085584641 | 50.85752295369553,4.361486424207688 | 50.85565368190626,4.362741698026658 | 50.854739336895925,4.366507519483567 | 50.85328332939455,4.365726973288662 | 50.856089508165894,4.355657382803344 | 50.858701239679924,4.34624065819702 }} {{IsPartOf|Brussels}} {{geo|50.8621|4.3562|zoom=15}}

{{pagebanner|Bruxelles Matonge en Couleurs 2009 002 (cropped).jpg|pgname=Matongé}} '''Matongé''' is a district in [[Brussels]], the capital of [[Belgium]], and home to its [[Africa]]n population originating from the [[Congo]]<!--which one?-->.
==Get in== {{mapframe | 50.8340 | 4.3644 | zoom=15}} {{mapshapes|Q506298}}<!--metro--> {{Mapshapes|Q117965|stroke-width=2}} <!-- Brussels S-train --> ===By metro=== {{marker|type=go|wikidata=Q2153197|name=Porte de Namur / Naamsepoort}} {{rint|brussels|2}}{{rint|brussels|6}} is located at the north edge of the district.
===By bus=== The Matonge stop is a little bit south east of the metro station.
==See== [[File:Matonge.jpg|thumb|Chéri Samba Porte de Namur, porte de l'amour?]] * {{see | name= Chéri Samba Porte de Namur, porte de l'amour | alt= | url= | email= | address=Chaussée d'Ixelles | lat=50.8377 | long=4.3619 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | image=Matonge.jpg | lastedit=2018-09-11 | content=Mural representing the African community }}
==Do== * {{do | name=Styx |alt=| url=http://www.cinenews.be | email= | address=Gewijde Boomstraat 72 | lat=50.832803 | long=4.363959 | directions={{station|Sint-Bonifaas|54|71|n09|n10}} | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= |lastedit=2018-09-10| content=Run by the cooperative nouveau cinema. Screens interesting films in their original version with French and Dutch subtitles. }} * {{do | name=Vendôme | url=http://www.cinema-vendome.be | email= | address=Waversesteenweg 18 | lat=50.837458 | long=4.36291 | directions={{station|Mantongé-Naamsepoort|54|71|n09|n10}} | phone=+32 2 502 37 00 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Another arthouse cinema. It's near the Porte de Namur (Naamsepoort) and acts as the metaphysical gateway to a lively African neighbourhood known locally as Matongé. }} * {{do | name=UGC Toison d'Or | alt= | url=https://www.ugc.be/cinema.html?id=1 | email= | address=Guldenvlieslaan 8 | lat=50.8377742 | long=4.3610574 | directions={{station|Mantongé-Naamsepoort|54|71|n09|n10}} | phone=+32 2 289 71 35 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2018-07-25 | content=Smaller UGC cinema playing the big blockbuster movies. }}
==Buy==
==Eat== * {{eat | name=Les Brassins | url= | email= | address=Rue Keyenveld-Keienveldstraat 36, Ixelles-Elsene | lat=50.835114 | long=4.361189 | directions= | phone=+32 2 512-6999 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Its crowd is mostly made out of young couples or students. Rich choice of beer, with more than 50 varieties on the menu, and good quality of food. In summer they have a few tables outside on a beautiful pedestrianized street. }}
In Ixelles-Elsene:
* {{eat | name=L'Ultime Atome | alt= | url=https://www.ultimeatome.be/en/ | email=contact@ultimeatome.be | address=Rue Saint-Boniface—Sint-Bonifaasstraat 14 | lat=50.835889 | long=4.364448 | directions= | phone=+32 2 513 48 84 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2017-05-30 | content=Increasingly chic, but still just about affordable brasserie, serving tasty food and drink from breakfast till late. }} * {{eat | name=Mano a Mano | alt= | url=http://www.manoamano.be/ | email=info@manoamano.be | address=Rue Saint-Boniface—Sint-Bonifaasstraat 8 | lat=50.835819 | long=4.364690 | directions= | phone=+32 2 502 08 01 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2017-05-30 | content=Italian restaurant. Good food, not too expensive. }} * {{eat | name=L'Amour Fou | alt= | url=https://www.lamourfou.be/ | email= | address=Chaussée d'Ixelles—Elsensesteenweg 185 | lat=50.832443 | long=4.366675 | directions= | phone=+32 2 325 73 53 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2017-05-30 | content=American diner-style bar and restaurant close to Place Fernand Cocq-Fernand Cocqplein. Advertises itself for its burgers and cocktails. }}
Some non-vegetarian restaurants that are particularly vegetarian-friendly:
* {{eat | name=El Turco | alt= | url=http://elturco.be | email= | address=Place de Londres-Londenplein 6 | lat=50.837758 | long=4.368465 | directions= | phone=+32 2 503 36 48 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M-F 11:30-15:00 and Tu-F 19:00-22:30 | price=€25 for all, excluding drinks | lastedit=2017-04-22 | content=Turkish-inspired buffet restaurant. Offers meats and fish, but the cold buffet is entirely vegetarian. }}
